public class Graph
extends java.lang.Object

Graph class which contains definition of a control flow graph and methods for reading-in a comma separated control flow graph from a file

Author:
Cory M. Lee

Consructor for graph class.

Parameters:
Nodes - - ArrayList of Strings, these are the names of the nodes.
Edge - - ArrayList of Edges, these are names of the Edges.
begin - - ArrayList of Pairs, these are the tuples of type Edge, Node. Pairs an edge with the node it begins on.
end - - ArrayList of Pairs, these are the tuples of type Edge, Node. Pairs an edge with the node it ends on.
numVisits - - Number of steps(in edges) you want to complete pathing through this graph.
StartPt - - the node where you want your path to start from. Must be contained in the ArrayList of Nodes or an exception will be thrown.
endPt - - the node where you want your path to end. Must be contained in the ArrayList of Nodes or an exception will be thrown.
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - - Exception is thrown when StartPt or Endpt are not contained within the ArrayList of Nodes.

readFile

public void readFile(java.lang.String inputFileName)
reads an input file and sets up the graph in question. format is as follows: Line# line-text. no trailing commas, no spaces. 0 Node1,Node2,Node3,Node4 // comma separated list of node names. 1 Edge1,Edge2,Edge3 // comma separated list of edge names 2 Node1 // name of start node. 3 Node4 // name of end node. 4 3 // number of steps you want to complete the path in.... in terms of edges. 5 Edge1,Node1/Edge2,Node2 // begin tupples 6 Edge1,Node1/Edge2,Node2

Parameters:
inputFileName -
